#X text 67 35 Here's a way tom implement a moving sum then an average with a patch. To the left in a simpler way with ELSE objects and to the right with Vanilla objects for the delay line and the accumulator. The idea is simple \, we subtract a signal to a delay line to remove samples after a time window. Then we sum it and average it. The main trick is to use [rpole~] as a signal accumulator \, where we keep suming the current value to the last input., f 70;
